{"type":"message","id":"62f97eca","parentId":"fff52e27","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:41:56.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing Skill Definitions**\n\nI am currently working on defining the `skills/log-reader/SKILL.md` file. The primary objective is to enable \"Skills Search (ClawHub)\" to install the most effective log-reading tool. The skill definition will be basic, to get the initial functionality working.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771162916119_157","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Log Reader Skill\n\n## Description\nA specialized utility for efficiently reading, filtering, and analyzing log files in the OpenClaw environment. Acts as a \"context-optimizer\" by extracting only relevant log lines based on time, severity, or keywords.\n\n## Tools\nThis skill uses standard `read` and `exec` tools but provides patterns for efficient log access.\n\n## Usage\n- **Filter by time:** `grep \"2024-02-15 12:\" logs/app.log`\n- **Tail logs:** `tail -n 100 logs/app.log`\n- **Error scan:** `grep -i \"error\" logs/app.log | tail -n 20`\n\n## Capabilities\n- Rapid log parsing\n- Context window optimization (only relevant lines)\n- Error aggregation\n\n## Metadata\n- **Version:** 1.0.0\n- **Author:** OpenClaw Fleet\n- **Tags:** logs, debugging, context-optimizer\n","file_path":"skills/log-reader/SKILL.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":74024,"output":279,"cacheRead":70639,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74303,"cost":{"input":0.14804799999999999,"output":0.0033480000000000003,"cacheRead":0.014127800000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.16552379999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771162909460}}
